Chemical-Specific Prevention Steps:



Prevention of accidental ammonia releases at Airgas an Air Liquide Company is accomplished through sound design and construction of the original refrigeration system, the specification and review of system modifications through a Management of Change Process (MOC), and the day-to-day operation and maintenance of the system.  This includes:



-  Compliance with industry standards and codes in effect at the time of initial construction and modification;

-  Performance of a thorough Process Hazard Analyses (PHA) once every five years using accurate Process Safety Information; 

-  Implementation of written operating procedures; 

-  Training and qualification of operators and maintenance personnel;  

-  Performance of preventive and corrective maintenance according to Airgas an Air Liquide Company  maintenance standards and system component manufacturer recommendations; 

-  Application of established auditing, inspection, management of change (MOC) and pre-start-up safety reviews(PSSR) programs; and

-  Use of qualified contractors for work on the system.

-  Use of safeguards that prevent, detect, or mitigate accidental releases of ammonia.
